# Performance and SEO Rules

Targets: Lighthouse Performance 95+, SEO 100, Best Practices 100. Core Web Vitals: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200ms.

## Performance

### Images

- Prefer inline SVG (illustrations, icons, patterns, logos) and CSS gradients — zero network cost, infinitely scalable
- For photographic placeholders use lightweight SVG data-URI placeholders, not external image services
- Any `<img>` MUST have explicit `width` and `height` (or `aspect-ratio` in CSS) to prevent CLS
- Below-the-fold images: `loading="lazy" decoding="async"`; the LCP/hero image must NOT be lazy-loaded (use `fetchpriority="high"` if it is an `<img>`)

### Fonts

- Default to the system font stack (zero cost). If a webfont is essential: embed via `@font-face` + `font-display: swap`, subset, WOFF2 only — never a render-blocking stylesheet `<link>`
- Avoid FOIT; size-adjust fallback metrics if the design is font-sensitive

### CSS / JS

- Single `<style>` in `<head>` (inherently render-non-blocking-critical), single `<script>` at end of `<body>`
- No external scripts, no third-party embeds by default
- Animate only `transform` and `opacity`; never animate layout properties (width/height/top/left)
- Use `IntersectionObserver` (not scroll listeners) for reveals; passive event listeners for any scroll/touch handlers
- Debounce/throttle resize handlers; prefer CSS-only solutions over JS where possible
- Avoid layout thrash: batch DOM reads/writes; use `requestAnimationFrame` for visual updates

### CLS discipline

- Reserve space for everything that loads or toggles (aspect-ratio boxes, min-heights on dynamic regions)
- No content insertion above existing content after load

## SEO

### Head (mandatory)

- `<title>` 50–60 chars; `<meta name="description">` 140–160 chars
- Canonical: `<link rel="canonical">` (use a placeholder domain comment if unknown)
- Open Graph: `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:type`, `og:url`, `og:image`
- Twitter: `twitter:card` (summary_large_image), `twitter:title`, `twitter:description`
- `<meta name="robots" content="index, follow">`

### Structured data

- JSON-LD `<script type="application/ld+json">` matched to site type: `Organization`/`WebSite` always; plus `Product`, `LocalBusiness`, `FAQPage`, `Service`, etc. as relevant

### Content

- Single `<h1>` containing the primary keyword/value proposition; descriptive heading hierarchy
- Descriptive link text (never "click here"); `rel="noopener"` on `target="_blank"` links
- Semantic HTML throughout — it is the SEO backbone of a static template
